  "body": "### What is it?\r\n\r\nWith the introduction of round trip request response in #1063 and #1089 we now can do very clean tracking of peer latency for various requests.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nLets update [`Peer.get_block_headers()`](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/f01c6563967f7f6c4c0903027d1c36c78016c776/p2p/peer.py#L636-L642) to track the following metrics about requests and responses.\r\n\r\n- round trip time\r\n- total number of objects in the response\r\n- total number of requests\r\n- average round trip time normalized for number of returned objects.\r\n\r\nThese metrics should be logged on a per-command (or maybe command pair?) basis, so that we have distinct metrics for each command we track.\r\n\r\nThen lets update the DEBUG log reporting of peers to include this information.  Something like:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nPeer: <peer-information-here>\r\n  - BlockHeaders: count=<total-num-requests> avg=<avg-round-trip-time> avg-time-per-obj=<normalized-round-trip-time-per-object-returned>\r\n```\r\n",
